SIMPLE: northeast
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Northeast
<hw>North`east"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The point between
the north and east, at an equal distance from each; the northeast part
or region.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Northeast</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Northeast
<hw>North`east"</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to the
northeast; proceeding toward the northeast, or coming from that point;
<as>as, a <ex>northeast</ex> course; a <ex>northeast</ex>
wind.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Northeast passage</b></col>, <cd>a passage or
communication by sea between the Atlantic and Pacific oceans along the
north coast of Asia.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Northeast</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Northeast
<hw>North`east"</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Toward the
northeast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Northeaster</ent>⟦br⟧
